      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:32:1",
      "text": [
        " الْحِنَّاءُ يَزِيدُ فِي مَاءِ الْوَجْهِ وَ يُكْثِرُ الشَّيْبَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Al Hakam, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The (application of) henna increase in the water of the face, and frequents the greying’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn al-Hakam who has said the following: “Abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Applying hair dye with henna increases the beauty of the face as well as gray hairs.”’ "
        ]
      }
